'''Margaret Sarfo''' (a yɛ frɛ no '''Peggy Oppong''', née '''Odame'''; 26 Ɔpɛpɔn 1957 – 8 Kotonimma 2014)<ref name="Kwei">{{Cite journal}}</ref> yɛ [[Ghana]] ni nwoma twerɛfo ne Nsɛmtwerɛfo. Ɔyɛ adwuma wɔ Graphic Communications Group Limited ɛsɔre  bɛyɛ koowaa krataa mu samufo ɛma The Mirror.<ref name="Bruinhorst">{{Cite web}}</ref><ref name="Bruinhorst"/>

== Abrabɔnfitiasɛ ne N'adesua mu nsɛm ==
Opanyin Daniel Odame ne ne yere wo Margaret Sarfo  afe 1957, ɛwɔ Mpraeso, Kwahu, a ɛwɔ Ghana anaafo mu.<ref name="Kwei">{{Cite journal}}</ref> Magaret Sarfo ɛkɔ sukuu wɔ   Adabraka, Accra, ɔwie yɛ no ɔtoa ne sukuu so wɔ  Okuapeman Secondary School, Akropong, ɛhɔ na onya  ne General Certificate of Education (GCE), Ordinary ne Advanced levels.<ref name="Kwei" />
Ɔsan nso toa ne  sukuu so wɔ  University of Ghana ɛwɔ afe 1979,ɔwie sukuu no gye na bordin krataa wɔ BA (Hons) wɔ brɔfo kasaa ne Russia kasaa mu.<ref name="Kwei" /> Ɔde afe baako sua ade wɔ Russia no,<ref name="Kwei" /><ref name="Bruinhorst">{{Cite web}}</ref> ɔsan nso ba University of Ghana ɛbɛ wie sukuu no gye na bordin krataa wɔ ne Diploma ne MPhil degrees wɔ nipa ho nkitahodie adesua.<ref name="Kwei" />

